"Ending welfare as we know it" has been a goal of federal, state and
European legislatures from the Reagan era through the Clinton years.
Some success is being made by reforming welfare, specifically,
limiting the time period of welfare eligibility and requiring
recipients to earn benefits through work or study.</SUM>
